    { type: "list", items: [
      "<strong>Ngorongoro Crater</strong> — A biodiversity hotspot",
      "<strong>Lake Manyara</strong> — Known for flamingos and waterfowl",
      "<strong>Rubondo Island</strong> — Rare island birding experience",
    ]},
    { type: "h2", content: "Uganda: The Realm of the Shoebill" },
    { type: "text", content: "Uganda's lush wetlands, forests, and lakes make it a top birding location. With over 1,000 species, it's the best place in the world to see the rare and prehistoric-looking <strong>Shoebill Stork</strong>." },
    { type: "image", src: "/images/shoebill-bird-wildlife-safari_blog.jpg", alt: "The prehistoric-looking Shoebill Stork in Uganda's wetlands", caption: "The Shoebill Stork is one of Africa's most sought-after bird sightings" },
    { type: "h3", content: "Mabamba Swamp" },
    { type: "text", content: "Located near Entebbe on the shores of Lake Victoria, this swamp is a <strong>must-visit</strong> for Shoebill sightings. Other notable species include:" },
    { type: "list", items: [
      "Blue-headed Coucal",
      "Blue-breasted Bee-eater",
      "White-winged Warbler",
    ]},
    { type: "h3", content: "Bwindi Impenetrable National Park" },
    { type: "text", content: "A UNESCO World Heritage Site, Bwindi is not just for gorilla trekking — it also offers spectacular birding with over <strong>350 species</strong>:" },
    { type: "list", items: [
      "Chapin's Flycatcher",
      "Short-tailed Warbler",
      "Kivu Ground Thrush",
    ]},
    { type: "h3", content: "More Birding Hotspots in Uganda" },
    { type: "list", items: [
      "<strong>Queen Elizabeth National Park</strong>",
      "<strong>Kibale Forest</strong> — Famous for chimpanzees and birds",
      "<strong>Semuliki National Park</strong> — Rich in Central African bird species",
    ]},
    { type: "h2", content: "Rwanda & Burundi: Forest Jewels of the Great Lakes" },
    { type: "text", content: "Though often overlooked, <strong>Rwanda</strong> and <strong>Burundi</strong> offer rewarding birding in compact and diverse areas." },
    { type: "image", src: "/images/small-bird-nature-watching-safari_blog.jpg", alt: "A small colorful bird in the forests of Rwanda", caption: "Rwanda's Nyungwe Forest is home to over 300 bird species" },
    { type: "h3", content: "Nyungwe National Park (Rwanda)" },
    { type: "text", content: "One of Africa's oldest rainforests, Nyungwe is home to over <strong>300 bird species</strong>, including:" },
    { type: "list", items: [
      "Red-collared Turaco",
      "Ruwenzori Blue Turaco",
      "Yellow-crested Helmetshrike",
    ]},
    { type: "h3", content: "Akagera National Park (Rwanda)" },
    { type: "text", content: "Akagera is ideal for wetland and savanna birds. Notable species:" },
    { type: "list", items: [
      "Shoebill",
      "Saddle-billed Stork",
      "African Skimmer",
    ]},
    { type: "h3", content: "Birding in Burundi" },
    { type: "list", items: [
      "<strong>Ruvubu National Park</strong> — Largest national park in Burundi",
      "<strong>Kibira National Park</strong> — Montane forest with rich birdlife",
    ]},
    { type: "h2", content: "Planning Your East African Birding Adventure" },
    { type: "text", content: "A successful East Africa birding trip depends on good planning." },
    { type: "h3", content: "Best Times to Go" },
    { type: "list", items: [
      "<strong>Dry seasons</strong> (December–March and June–September) are best for visibility and travel ease",
      "<strong>Migration periods</strong> offer chances to see rare migrants",
    ]},
    { type: "h3", content: "Birding Essentials" },
    { type: "list", items: [
      "Binoculars (8x42 recommended)",
      "Field guide — <em>Birds of East Africa</em> by Stevenson & Fanshawe",
      "Camera with zoom lens",
      "Notebook or birding app for logging sightings",
    ]},
    { type: "h3", content: "Hire a Local Guide" },
    { type: "text", content: "Local bird guides know the best spots, calls, and behaviors. At <strong>Simbali Wild Safaris</strong>, our expert guides can help you identify the hot spots and make the most of your birding adventure." },
    { type: "h2", content: "Safety and Travel Tips" },
    { type: "list", items: [
      "Check visa requirements for each country",
      "Ensure vaccinations (Yellow Fever, Hepatitis, etc.)",
      "Pack light but bring layers for varying climates",
      "Stay in eco-lodges for sustainable travel",
    ]},
    { type: "h2", content: "Conclusion" },
    { type: "text", content: "Whether you're hoping to glimpse the <strong>Shoebill</strong> in Uganda, watch flamingos at Lake Nakuru, or track endemics in the Taita Hills, <strong>East Africa birding</strong> is truly a dream experience." },
    { type: "text", content: "So pack your binoculars, download your birding checklist, and get ready to explore one of the richest birding regions on the planet! <a href=\"/contact\" class=\"text-olive underline font-semibold\">Contact Simbali Wild Safaris</a> to plan your ultimate birding adventure." },
  ],
  "wildebeest-migration-an-epic-safari-adventure": [
    { type: "text", content: "Every year, over a million wildebeest embark on a treacherous journey across the vast Serengeti-Mara ecosystem in Tanzania and Kenya. The Great Migration is a breathtaking journey many dream of seeing in person. It's truly a <strong>once-in-a-lifetime experience</strong>." },
    { type: "image", src: "/images/wildebeest-migration-herd-safari_blog.jpg", alt: "Massive herd of wildebeest stretching across the golden Serengeti plains", caption: "The sheer scale of the migration — over 1.5 million animals on the move" },
    { type: "h2", content: "Understanding the Wildebeest Migration Route" },
    { type: "text", content: "The wildebeest migration is a continuous cyclical journey, driven by the ever-changing availability of water and fresh grazing grounds. These animals travel over <strong>1,800 miles</strong> across Tanzania's Serengeti and Kenya's Maasai Mara." },
    { type: "text", content: "The migration begins in southern Serengeti around January. As thousands of wildebeest give birth during the calving season — a breathtaking sight." },
    { type: "text", content: "As the rains fade and grass thins out, the wildebeest move north in search of fresh greenery. Their journey leads them across dangerous rivers, where they face strong currents and the constant threat of crocodiles." },
    { type: "image", src: "/images/wildebeest-rocky-river-crossing-safari_blog.jpg", alt: "Dramatic wildebeest crossing a rocky river during the migration", caption: "The river crossings are the most dramatic — and dangerous — part of the migration" },
    { type: "h2", content: "The Great Migration: A Life-or-Death Journey" },
    { type: "text", content: "The wildebeest migration is more than a scenic journey. It's a life-or-death trek that highlights nature's raw power and the fight for survival. Along the way, the wildebeest face numerous dangers and obstacles that test their endurance and resilience." },
    { type: "text", content: "One of the most iconic and heart-wrenching events of the migration is the river crossings. As the herds approach the swollen rivers, a palpable tension builds, and the wildebeest hesitate, sensing the danger that lies ahead. Eventually, the sheer weight of the massive herd pushes the first brave individuals into the water, and the rest follow in a frenzied stampede." },
    { type: "text", content: "The river crossings are a true spectacle of nature's drama, with wildebeest struggling against the powerful currents, while crocodiles and other predators lie in wait, ready to claim their share of the bounty. The sheer chaos and intensity of these crossings are both awe-inspiring and heart-wrenching, leaving spectators on the edge of their seats." },
    { type: "text", content: "Beyond the river crossings, the wildebeest must also contend with other formidable obstacles, such as steep ravines, rugged terrain, and the ever-present threat of predators like lions, hyenas, and cheetahs. These skilled hunters take advantage of the vulnerability of the wildebeest during their journey, picking off the weak, the young, and the stragglers in a never-ending cycle of life and death." },
    { type: "h2", content: "When to Witness the Wildebeest Migration" },
    { type: "text", content: "Timing is crucial when it comes to witnessing the wildebeest migration in all its glory. The migration is a year-round event, but certain periods offer more spectacular sights than others." },
    { type: "h3", content: "The Calving Season (January – March)" },
    { type: "text", content: "The calving season, which typically occurs between late January and early March, is an extraordinary time to witness the wildebeest migration. During this period, hundreds of thousands of wildebeest congregate in the southern plains of the Serengeti to give birth to their calves. The sight of newborn calves taking their first wobbly steps amidst the vast herds is a truly heartwarming and unforgettable experience." },
    { type: "h3", content: "The River Crossings (June – July)" },
    { type: "text", content: "One of the most dramatic and highly anticipated events of the migration is the river crossings, which typically occur between June and July. During this time, the wildebeest herds must navigate the treacherous waters of the Mara River, braving powerful currents and the ever-present threat of crocodile attacks. The sheer intensity and chaos of these crossings make for an adrenaline-pumping and unforgettable experience." },
    { type: "h3", content: "The Northward Trek (August – October)" },
    { type: "text", content: "As the dry season sets in, the wildebeest begin their northward journey towards the lush grazing grounds of the Maasai Mara National Reserve in Kenya. This period, from August to October, offers ample opportunities to witness the massive herds on the move, grazing in the open plains and interacting with other iconic African wildlife species." },
    { type: "h2", content: "Planning Your Wildebeest Migration Safari" },
    { type: "text", content: "Witnessing the wildebeest migration is a bucket list experience for many, but it requires careful planning and preparation. Here are some tips to help you make the most of your wildebeest migration safari:" },
    { type: "list", items: [
      "<strong>Choose the Right Time:</strong> Decide on the specific event or phase of the migration you wish to witness, and plan your trip accordingly. Keep in mind that the migration is a fluid event, and the timing can vary from year to year.",
      "<strong>Book Early:</strong> Popular safari camps and lodges in the Serengeti and Maasai Mara can fill up quickly, especially during peak migration periods. Use our <a href=\"/services\" class=\"text-olive underline\">Tailored Safari packages</a> and Book well in advance to secure your spot.",
      "<strong>Hire a Knowledgeable Guide:</strong> Our skill and experience safari guide can make all the difference in your migration experience. We will not only help you navigate the best viewing spots but also provide invaluable insights into the behavior and dynamics of the wildebeest herds.",
      "<strong>Pack Appropriately:</strong> The Serengeti and Maasai Mara can be hot and dusty during the dry season, and the terrain can be rugged. Pack lightweight, breathable clothing, sturdy hiking shoes, and plenty of sunscreen and insect repellent.",
      "<strong>Be Prepared for Long Days:</strong> Witnessing the wildebeest migration often involves long hours in a safari vehicle, navigating rough terrain and waiting patiently for the herds to move or for river crossings to occur. Be prepared for long days and early starts to make the most of your <a href=\"/itineraries\" class=\"text-olive underline\">Wonders of the Natural World</a>.",
      "<strong>Respect the Environment:</strong> The wildebeest migration is a fragile and delicate ecosystem. Follow all guidelines and regulations set by the national parks and your safari operators to minimize your impact on the environment and the wildlife.",
    ]},
    { type: "h2", content: "Conservation and the Future of the Migration" },
    { type: "text", content: "The Great Wildebeest Migration isn't just an amazing sight — it's a key part of keeping the Serengeti-Mara ecosystem alive and healthy. Every year, over a million wildebeests move across the plains, supporting a wide variety of animals, from lions and hyenas to birds and insects." },
    { type: "text", content: "But this natural wonder is under threat. Habitat loss, poaching, and climate change are putting pressure on the migration routes. As nearby human populations grow, the wildebeests' grazing lands and paths are shrinking, causing more conflict and damage to the ecosystem." },
    { type: "text", content: "Thankfully, organizations like the <strong>Frankfurt Zoological Society</strong>, the <strong>Serengeti Wildlife Research Institute</strong>, and <strong>Tanzania's National Parks Authority</strong> are working hard to protect the migration. They run anti-poaching patrols, educate local communities, and help create safe corridors for the animals to travel." },
    { type: "text", content: "Still, they can't do it alone. Protecting the wildebeest migration depends on support from people like you — travelers, nature lovers, and anyone who cares about our planet." },
    { type: "text", content: "When you book your safari with eco-friendly tour operators and respect the wildlife, you're helping preserve this incredible event." },
    { type: "text", content: "Your trip becomes more than just a once-in-a-lifetime adventure — it becomes part of the effort to keep the wildebeest migration alive for future generations." },
    { type: "text", content: "At <strong>Simbali Wild Safaris</strong>, we believe in responsible tourism that respects wildlife and supports local communities. We follow strict guidelines to minimize our impact, support conservation efforts, and ensure that the migration can be enjoyed by future generations. <a href=\"/contact\" class=\"text-olive underline font-semibold\">Contact us today</a> to start planning your migration safari!" },
  ],
};

const { slug } = Astro.params;
const { post } = Astro.props;
const content = blogContent[slug] || [];
const related = relatedSafaris[slug] || [];
const allSlugs = ["amboseli-national-park-elephants-kilimanjaro", "wonders-of-kenyas-great-rift-valley", "east-africa-birding-guide", "wildebeest-migration-an-epic-safari-adventure"];
const otherSlugs = allSlugs.filter(s => s !== slug);
---

<MainLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Simbali Wild Safaris Blog`}
  description={post.description}
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="canonical" href={`https://simbaliwildsafaris.com/blog/${slug}/`} />
    <meta property="og:title" content={`${post.title} | Simbali Wild Safaris`} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={post.description} />
    <meta property="og:type" content="article" />
    <meta property="og:url" content={`https://simbaliwildsafaris.com/blog/${slug}/`} />
    <meta property="og:image" content={`https://simbaliwildsafaris.com${post.img}`} />
    <meta property="article:published_time" content={post.date} />
    <meta property="article:section" content={post.cat} />
    {post.tags.map(tag => <meta property="article:tag" content={tag} />)}
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BlogPosting",
      "headline": post.title,
      "description": post.description,
      "image": `https://simbaliwildsafaris.com${post.img}`,
      "datePublished": post.date,
      "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": post.author },
      "publisher": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Simbali Wild Safaris",
        "logo": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://simbaliwildsafaris.com/images/simbali-favicon.png" }
      },
      "mainEntityOfPage": {
        "@type": "WebPage",
        "@id": `https://simbaliwildsafaris.com/blog/${slug}/`
      }
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  {/* Hero */}
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <OptimizedImage src={post.img} alt={post.imgAlt} class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="eager" />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/50" />
    </div>
    <div class="relative container-main py-20 md:py-28">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center anim-fade-up">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-3 text-white/70 text-sm mb-4">
          <span class="bg-white/20 backdrop-blur px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider">{post.cat}</span>
          <span>{post.date}</span>
          <span>/</span>
          <span>{post.readTime}</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-belleza text-3xl md:text-5xl tracking-[0.08em] uppercase text-white leading-tight mb-4">{post.title}</h1>
        <p class="text-white/80 text-base md:text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">{post.description}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Article */}
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container-main max-w-4xl">
      <article class="prose-blog max-w-none">
        {content.map((block) => {
          if (block.type === 'h2') return <h2 class="font-belleza text-2xl md:text-3xl tracking-[0.08em] uppercase mt-12 mb-5 text-[#1a1a1a]" set:html={block.content} />;
          if (block.type === 'h3') return <h3 class="font-belleza text-xl md:text-2xl tracking-[0.06em] uppercase mt-8 mb-4 text-[#1a1a1a]" set:html={block.content} />;
          if (block.type === 'text') return <p class="text-[#444] leading-[1.8] mb-5 text-[15px]" set:html={block.content} />;
          if (block.type === 'quote') return (
            <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-olive bg-sage/20 pl-6 pr-4 py-5 my-8 rounded-r-xl">
              <p class="text-[#555] italic text-lg leading-relaxed">"{block.content}"</p>
            </blockquote>
          );
          if (block.type === 'list') return (
            <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
              {block.items?.map(item => <li class="text-[#444] text-[15px] leading-[1.8] flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-olive flex-shrink-0 mt-1.5 text-xs">&#9654;</span><span set:html={item} /></li>)}
            </ul>
          );
          if (block.type === 'image') return (
            <figure class="my-8 anim-scale-in">
              <OptimizedImage src={block.src} alt={block.alt} class="w-full h-64 md:h-80 object-cover rounded-xl" loading="lazy" />
              {block.caption && <figcaption class="text-center text-[#999] text-sm mt-2 italic">{block.caption}</figcaption>}
            </figure>
          );
          return null;
        })}
      </article>

      {/* Tags */}
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-10 pt-8 border-t border-gray-100">
        {post.tags.map(tag => <span class="text-xs text-[#666] bg-[#f5f7f3] px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full">{tag}</span>)}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Related Safaris */}
  {related.length > 0 && (
    <section class="py-16 bg-sage/20">
      <div class="container-main max-w-4xl">
        <h2 class="font-belleza text-2xl tracking-[0.1em] uppercase mb-8 text-center anim-fade-up">Related Safari Itineraries</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          {related.map((safari, i) => (
            <a href={safari.url} class={`group bg-white rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-gray-100 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 flex flex-col hover-lift anim-fade-up anim-delay-${i + 1}`}>
              <div class="relative overflow-hidden h-48">
                <OptimizedImage src={safari.img} alt={safari.title} class="w-full h-full object-cover group-hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-500" loading="lazy" />
                <div class="absolute top-3 right-3 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur text-olive text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full">{safari.duration}</div>
              </div>
              <div class="p-5 flex flex-col flex-1">
                <h3 class="font-belleza text-lg tracking-[0.06em] uppercase mb-1">{safari.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-olive font-semibold text-sm">{safari.price}</p>
                <span class="text-olive text-xs font-semibold mt-3 group-hover:underline inline-flex items-center gap-1">View Itinerary <span>&rarr;</span></span>
              </div>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  )}

  {/* More Stories */}
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container-main max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="font-belleza text-2xl tracking-[0.1em] uppercase mb-8 text-center anim-fade-up">More Safari Stories</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {otherSlugs.map((otherSlug, idx) => {
          const otherPosts = {
            "amboseli-national-park-elephants-kilimanjaro": { title: "Amboseli National Park: Where Giants Roam", img: "/images/african-elephant-savanna-simbali-wild-safaris.jpg", excerpt: "Explore Kenya's elephant country, Kilimanjaro views, swamps, seasons, and photography tips." },
            "wonders-of-kenyas-great-rift-valley": { title: "Great Rift Valley Kenya: Nature, Culture & Adventure", img: "/images/serene-lakeside-mountain-landscape_blog.jpg", excerpt: "Discover dramatic escarpments, flamingo-filled lakes and volcanic craters." },
            "east-africa-birding-guide": { title: "East Africa Birding Guide", img: "/images/raptor-bird-flying-clear-sky_blog.jpg", excerpt: "Over 1,500 bird species across Kenya, Tanzania, Uganda and beyond." },
            "wildebeest-migration-an-epic-safari-adventure": { title: "The Great Wildebeest Migration", img: "/images/wildebeest-river-crossing-safari-migration_blog.jpg", excerpt: "Witness over a million wildebeest thunder across the Serengeti-Maasai Mara." },
          };
          const op = otherPosts[otherSlug];
          return (
            <a href={`/blog/${otherSlug}`} class={`group flex gap-4 items-start hover:bg-sage/10 p-3 rounded-xl transition-colors anim-fade-up anim-delay-${idx + 1}`}>
              <OptimizedImage src={op.img} alt={op.title} class="w-24 h-24 rounded-lg object-cover flex-shrink-0 group-hover:scale-105 transition-transform" loading="lazy" />
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-belleza text-base tracking-[0.06em] uppercase leading-snug mb-1 group-hover:text-olive transition-colors">{op.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-[#777] text-sm leading-relaxed">{op.excerpt}</p>
              </div>
            </a>
          );
        })}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* CTA */}
  <section class="py-20 bg-olive">
    <div class="container-main text-center anim-fade-up">
      <h2 class="font-belleza text-2xl md:text-3xl tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-white mb-4">Ready to Experience This?</h2>
      <p class="text-white/70 max-w-xl mx-auto mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        Let Simbali Wild Safaris craft your perfect African adventure. From the Great Migration to the Great Rift Valley, we'll design a journey you'll never forget.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary btn-pulse bg-white text-olive hover:bg-sage inline-flex">Plan Your Safari</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
